just_use test_dsl_conformance.py

# label: TOOL
# role: Python runner for shared DSL conformance fixtures

Reads `conformance_fixtures.json` (emitted by `cmd/fixturegen`
from `games/lynrummy/conformance/scenarios/*.dsl`) and dispatches
each scenario by op. No framework — plain Python asserts, one
PASS/FAIL line per scenario.

Python is interpreted, so this runner is the *only* Python test
artifact; the JSON file is the compiled form of the DSL. No
Python codegen.

## Supported ops

- `build_suggestions` — compares strategy.enumerate_plays output
  to expected trick_id + hand_cards rows. (DSL op name stays
  `build_suggestions` — shared concept with Elm, where it feeds
  the human-facing hint surface. Python's function is
  `enumerate_plays` since the agent doesn't suggest.)
- `hint_invariant` — calls the named emitter, applies its
  primitives, asserts every resulting stack classifies as a
  complete group (set / pure_run / rb_run).

## Pointers

- Enumerate-and-bridge cohort: same fixtures drive the Elm
  generated `DslConformanceTest.elm` tests. Divergence across
  languages surfaces as different pass/fail counts.
- Regenerate fixtures: `go run ./cmd/fixturegen ./games/lynrummy/conformance/scenarios/*.dsl`.

